Create Kotlin program that read three integers from the keyboard. The program prints the largest number to the screen.


Example output:
Type the first number: 
-5
Type the second number: 
0
Type the third number: 
3
The largest number = 3
The verification of program output does not account for whitespace characters like "\n", "\t" and " "

//Solution
fun main(args: Array<String>) {
	println("Type the first number:")
	var num1 = readLine()!!
	println("Type the second number:")
	var num2 = readLine()!!
	println("Type the third number:")
	var num3 = readLine()!!
	if ( num1 >= num2 && num1 >= num3) {
	println("The largest number = $num1")
	} else if (num2 > num1 && num2 >= num3){
	println("The largest number = $num2")
	} else{
	println("The largest number = $num3")
	}
}
